{
  "stem": "15962.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The 5,000 people who arrived with the first transport.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were the second transport.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The reason we all thought-- or the theory was that we were in this camp, children, old people, families together.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was called [GERMAN], the family camp.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Is that the Germans were negotiating with the [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] [GERMAN], the Red-- Red Cross, which was a Swiss volunteer organization.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "To show them that the rumors that people are sent to gas chambers and only men and women that were capable of hard work were spared.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They were trying to dispel this-- this image, and wanted the Swiss Red Cross to visit the camp.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they thought that if they kept us together, we would be a proof to them that they do not kill children and women.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Such a visit did occur in 1944 in Terezin, in Theresienstadt, at which time they literally cleaned up parts of the ghetto and in-- managed to fool the Red Cross, and believe that the Jews have a paradise in Terezin.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They finally decided that they did not want to bring them into Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And in March, they took the 5,000 men, women, and children into a adjacent camp.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were there one night, and during the night they loaded them up in-- into trucks and took them away.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They actually just took them around the camp and into the gas chambers.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "This Fredy Hirsch, that was the youth organizer, probably knew what was awaiting them, and he took some poison and died before he was sent to the gas chambers.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In his late 30s.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] He was a very charismatic person.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
